entry.title: Air Quality Alert issued July 26 at 7:30AM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT
entry.summary:
AQAMT
The Montana Department of Environmental Quality has issued an air quality alert for Beaverhead, Deer Lodge, Granite, Madison, Ravalli, and Silver Bow counties in effect until 8AM 7/27/2024 elevated particulate levels from wildfire smoke This alert will be updated again at 800am 7/27/2024.
An Air Quality Alert means that particulates have been trending upwards and that an exceedence of the 24 hour National Ambient Air Quality Standard (NAAQS) has occurred or may occur in the near future.
As of 7AM, Particulate levels in Hamilton are Very Unhealthy
As of 7AM, Particulate levels in Butte are Unhealthy for Sensitive Groups
As of 7AM, Particulate levels in Darby are Moderate
When air quality is Very Unhealthy... State and local health officials recommend that people with respiratory or heart disease, the elderly, and children should avoid any outdoor activity; everyone else should avoid prolonged exertion.
When air quality is Unhealthy for Sensitive Groups... State and local health officials recommend that people with respiratory or heart disease, the elderly and children should limit prolonged exertion.
When air quality is Moderate... State and local health officials recommend that unusually sensitive people should consider reducing prolonged or heavy exertion.
For more information visit the Montana Department of Environmental Quality at http://todaysair.mtdeq.us

entry.title: Air Quality Alert issued July 25 at 9:40PM MST by NWS Tucson AZ
entry.summary:
The Arizona Department of Environmental Quality (ADEQ) has issued an Ozone (OZ) High Pollution Advisory for the Tucson Metro area Friday.

entry.title: Flood Advisory issued July 25 at 9:04AM AKDT until July 26 at 4:00PM AKDT by NWS Juneau AK
entry.summary:
* WHAT...Flooding caused by rain and snowmelt continues.
* WHERE...The Chilkat River near areas around mile post 14 and 24 of the Haines Highway, near Klukwan and the Chilkat River bridge.
* WHEN...Until 400 PM AKDT Friday.
* IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas. River flows are elevated.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 902 AM AKDT, river gauge reports indicate rises in water levels from rain and snowmelt in areas around mile post 14 and 24 of the Haines Highway, near Klukwan and the Chilkat River Bridge. Minor flooding is ongoing, especially near the Chilkat River. Flooding impacts will continue.
- For Chilkat River at Klukwan: At 8:00am the stage was 127.9 feet. Flood Stage is 126.0 feet. Forecast: A crest around 128.1 feet is expected today. Water levels are projected to crest today and begin going down late this afternoon, falling below minor flood stage Friday evening.
Impacts: At 127.5 feet: Lower elevations in backyards along the Chilkat River in Klukwan will be underwater, and a river access road, smokehouses and storage sheds will flood. Bank erosion is expected to increase near Jilkaat Kwan Cultural Heritage Center Campus Traditional Knowledge camp.
At 128.0 feet: Water will begin to flow over the driveway into the property of Chilkat River Adventures just upstream of the Haines Highway Chilkat River bridge. Minor flooding may occur near mile post 14 and 25 boat launches along with minor flooding of Porcupine Road. Flooding of backyards along the Chilkat River in Klukwan will get worse.
